      "content": "If you're feeling completely well and your doctor has prescribed a 10-day course, it's likely because they've weighed the risks and benefits of taking the full course. Doctors often recommend finishing all the medication to avoid potential relapse and antibiotic resistance. Call your doctor and explain your situation; they'll guide you on whether you can stop once you're feeling better or need to finish the course. It's always best to follow their professional advice.",
